# Engine vs content

This repo is **vtt-core** (tactical VTT engine). Hellpiercers IP lives in `@gaem/hellpiercers-content` (`packages/hellpiercers-content`), registered at product boot.

## Dependency matrix

| Package | May depend on `@gaem/hellpiercers-content`? |
|---------|-----------------------------------------------|
| `@gaem/shared` | **No** |
| `@gaem/client` / `@gaem/server` / `@gaem/cf-worker` | **Yes** (product boots) |

Shared must not import the content package. Product packages side-effect-register at boot. Shared/client Vitest use fixture pack; HP suites live in `@gaem/hellpiercers-content`.

## Decisions (locked)

- Content = workspace package today; private npm/git dependency later (same name/exports). **Sync register-once** at boot (not runtime KV packs).
- Product boots: `@gaem/hellpiercers-content/register` (+ client `./register-client`). Never `@gaem/shared/register-hellpiercers`.
- Named combat implementations live in the content package and register via `CombatHookContribution.modules` + hooks; shared dispatches with `combatMod(key)`. Client UI helpers use `@gaem/hellpiercers-content/combat-ui`.
- Engine CI / shared Vitest target: fixture catalogs; content package owns HP tests. Product/e2e registers Hellpiercers.
- npm scope remains `@gaem/*` until explicitly renamed.
- Sibling copy `/Users/lindenholt/code/gaem` is historical — **do new work here**.
- Nested `GameState.campaign` (parent #2) is done. Sheet/pack-version KV migrations remain parent #7 — not required for content-pack A–E completion.

